    "## Example Walkthrough\n",
    "\n",
    "Suppose image: A dog sitting beside a bicycle\n",
    "\n",
    "* Input: `800×800`\n",
    "* Selective Search: `2000 proposals`\n",
    "      ```text\n",
    "      R1: dog area\n",
    "      R2: bicycle area\n",
    "      R3: sky\n",
    "      R4: grass\n",
    "      ```\n",
    "3. Whole image: `800×800` passes through CNN:\n",
    "      * Feature map:\n",
    "            $$\n",
    "            50×50×512\n",
    "            $$\n",
    "\n",
    "4. ROI projection:\n",
    "      ```text\n",
    "      R1→feature map region\n",
    "      R2→feature map region\n",
    "      ```\n",
    "5. ROI pooling:\n",
    "      ```text\n",
    "      R1→7×7×512\n",
    "      R2→7×7×512\n",
    "      ```\n",
    "\n",
    "6. Classification:\n",
    "      ```text\n",
    "      R1:\n",
    "      Dog=.98\n",
    "      Bike=.01\n",
    "\n",
    "      R2:\n",
    "      Dog=.02\n",
    "      Bike=.95\n",
    "      ```\n",
    "7. Bounding box refinement:\n",
    "      ```text\n",
    "      Dog box adjusted\n",
    "      Bike box adjusted\n",
    "      ```\n",
    "8. Final result:\n",
    "      ```text\n",
    "      Dog      [x1,y1,x2,y2]\n",
    "      Bicycle  [x1,y1,x2,y2]\n",
    "      ```\n",
    "\n",
    "## Charecterstics\n",
    "\n",
    "### Why Fast R-CNN Is Faster\n",
    "\n",
    "R-CNN:\n",
    "\n",
    "* 2000 proposals\n",
    "* →2000 CNN computations\n",
    "\n",
    "Fast R-CNN:\n",
    "\n",
    "* 1 image\n",
    "* 1 CNN computation\n",
    "\n",
    "Feature maps are reused.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Speed Comparison\n",
    "\n",
    "Approximate values:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Method     |  Training |   Test Speed |\n",
    "| ---------- | --------: | -----------: |\n",
    "| R-CNN      | Very slow |  ~47 s/image |\n",
    "| Fast R-CNN |    Faster | ~0.3 s/image |\n",
    "\n",
    "Huge improvement.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Advantages\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Shared computation: CNN runs once.\n",
    "2. End-to-end learning: Single-stage optimization.\n",
    "3. Better accuracy: Joint optimization improves results.\n",
    "4. No feature storage\n",
    "      * R-CNN stored CNN features on disk.\n",
    "      * Fast R-CNN computes features directly.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Limitations\n",
    "\n",
    "Fast R-CNN still uses: Selective Search\n",
    "      * Selective Search itself is slow: `≈2 seconds/image`\n",
    "\n",
    "Even though CNN became fast, proposal generation remained a bottleneck.\n",
    "\n",
    "This limitation led to the development of Faster R-CNN, which replaced Selective Search with a Region Proposal Network (RPN).\n",
    "\n",
    "### Comparison: R-CNN vs Fast R-CNN\n",
    "\n",
    "| Feature          | R-CNN            | Fast R-CNN       |\n",
    "| ---------------- | ---------------- | ---------------- |\n",
    "| CNN runs         | 2000 times       | 1 time           |\n",
    "| Classifier       | SVM              | Softmax          |\n",
    "| Training         | Multi-stage      | End-to-end       |\n",
    "| Feature storage  | Required         | Not required     |\n",
    "\n",
    "# Faster R-CNN\n",
    "\n",
    "Faster R-CNN is an object detection architecture introduced in 2015 by Shaoqing Ren, Kaiming He, Ross Girshick, and Jian Sun.\n",
    "\n",
    "It improves Fast R-CNN by solving its biggest bottleneck:\n",
    "\n",
    "> Fast R-CNN still relied on **Selective Search**, which was computationally expensive.\n",
    "\n",
    "Faster R-CNN replaces Selective Search with a **Region Proposal Network (RPN)** that learns to generate object proposals directly from CNN feature maps.\n",
    "\n",
    "This makes the entire system nearly end-to-end and significantly faster.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Evolution of R-CNN Family\n",
    "\n",
    "```text\n",
    "R-CNN\n",
    " ↓\n",
    "Fast R-CNN\n",
    " ↓\n",
    "Faster R-CNN\n",
    " ↓\n",
    "Mask R-CNN\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "| Method       | Proposal Method               | Main Improvement / Issue Solved                                                                      | Output                      |\n",
    "| ------------ | ----------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------- |\n",
    "| R-CNN        | Selective Search              | CNN had to run thousands of times on cropped regions → very slow                                     | Class + bounding box        |\n",
    "| Fast R-CNN   | Selective Search              | Single CNN feature map for entire image → faster training/inference, but Selective Search still slow | Class + bounding box        |\n",
    "| Faster R-CNN | RPN (Region Proposal Network) | Replaced Selective Search with learned proposal generation                                           | Class + bounding box        |\n",
    "| Mask R-CNN   | RPN + ROI Align               | Fixed ROI Pooling misalignment using ROI Align and added instance segmentation branch                | Class + bounding box + mask |\n",
    "\n",
    "### Core Idea of Faster R-CNN\n",
    "\n",
    "Instead of:\n",
    "\n",
    "```text\n",
    "Image\n",
    "   ↓\n",
    "Selective Search\n",
    "   ↓\n",
    "Region proposals\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Faster R-CNN uses:\n",
    "\n",
    "```text\n",
    "Image\n",
    "   ↓\n",
    "CNN Feature Map\n",
    "   ↓\n",
    "Region Proposal Network\n",
    "   ↓\n",
    "Region proposals\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "The network itself learns where objects might exist.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Faster R-CNN Architecture\n",
    "\n",
    "![Faster R-CNN Architecture](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/masum184e/handbook-old/removed/images/cnn/faster_r_cnn.png)\n",
    "\n",
    "Pipeline:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Input Image\n",
    "2. Convolutional Layers\n",
    "3. Shared Feature Map\n",
    "4. Region Proposal Network\n",
    "5. ROI Pooling\n",
    "6. Fully Connected Layers\n",
    "7. Classification + Bounding Box Regression\n",
    "8. Final Detection\n",
    "\n",
    "A key point:\n",
    "\n",
    "The CNN feature map is **shared** between:\n",
    "\n",
    "* Region Proposal Network\n",
    "* Object detector\n",
    "\n",
    "This reduces duplicate computation.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Input Image\n",
    "\n",
    "Suppose input image: Dog sitting beside bicycle\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "800×600\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Image enters CNN:\n",
    "\n",
    "Examples:\n",
    "\n",
    "* VGG\n",
    "* ResNet\n",
    "* ZF-Net\n",
    "\n",
    "CNN extracts visual features.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Generate Feature Map\n",
    "\n",
    "Convolutional layers transform:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "800×600×3\n",
    "$$\n",
    "into:\n",
    "$$\n",
    "50×38×512\n",
    "$$\n",
    "Feature map contains:\n",
    "\n",
    "* edges\n",
    "* textures\n",
    "* shapes\n",
    "* object parts\n",
    "\n",
    "Instead of processing pixels directly, all later operations work on this compact representation.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Region Proposal Network (RPN)\n",
    "\n",
    "This is the major innovation. RPN slides a small network over the feature map.\n",
    "\n",
    "```text\n",
    "     Feature Map\n",
    "         ↓\n",
    "      3×3 Conv\n",
    "         ↓\n",
    "    Two branches\n",
    "      ↙      ↘\n",
    "Objectness   Box Regression\n",
    "Score\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "The RPN predicts:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Whether an object exists\n",
    "2. Bounding box coordinates\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Sliding Window Operation\n",
    "\n",
    "Suppose feature map:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "50×38\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "RPN moves:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "3×3 \n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "window across all locations.\n",
    "\n",
    "At each location: Position (x,y)\n",
    "\n",
    "RPN asks:\n",
    "\n",
    "> Is there an object here?\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Anchor Boxes\n",
    "\n",
    "RPN does not predict arbitrary boxes. Instead it starts with predefined **anchor boxes**.\n",
    "\n",
    "At one location: 9 anchors:\n",
    "\n",
    "```text\n",
    "3 scales:\n",
    "128×128\n",
    "256×256\n",
    "512×512\n",
    "\n",
    "3 aspect ratios:\n",
    "1:1\n",
    "1:2\n",
    "2:1\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Total: $3×3=9$ anchors\n",
    "\n",
    "Example:\n",
    "\n",
    "```text\n",
    "Anchor1 = square\n",
    "Anchor2 = tall rectangle\n",
    "Anchor3 = wide rectangle\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "These act as candidate boxes.\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Example Anchor Layout\n",
    "\n",
    "At one image position:\n",
    "\n",
    "```text\n",
    "        □\n",
    "   ▭    □    ▯\n",
    "        □\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Different shapes capture different object types:\n",
    "\n",
    "* person → tall\n",
    "* car → wide\n",
    "* ball → square\n",
    "\n",
    "### Objectness Prediction\n",
    "\n",
    "For every anchor RPN predicts: `Object score`\n",
    "\n",
    "| Anchor | Probability |\n",
